se the noise, the entropy to measure analog qbits. one day i will burn the quantum engine into a FPGA circuit. making the quantum engine a synthetic quantum processor. but that is a bit far away, i wanna build my one resonator so i could see if all of this works for real. but the simulated resonator and the quantum engine works!i also made with my quantum engine and microqiskit, so called quantum ants.I emulated a 6502 microprocessor as the brain of the ants but i use the resonator, that allows the ants to”feel” the resonance and behaves randomly, well like in real life. because of this, I dont use #random library anymore, i use the resonator(well in this case the resonator is simulated through a quantum circuit.) and look how the ants behave and moves\ As you look at the ants how they move, does not look like its emergent behavior?this video is a bit bad, sorry about that(hey, that rhymed xD)I gave them an ant queen that makes more ants, my next phase is give the queen egg logic so the other ants have something do to this is a virtual ant farm if you will. But these little ants,they are the prototype for my npc’s in my simulated quantum universe.World’s first quantum pixel\ but my quantum engine also has another application…I generated quantum pixels, and i even generated a planet with these quantum pixelsthese quantum pixels are visual noise, like the old analog tv noise. but i manipulate these white noise to create graphics…so i call these quantum pixels\ \ in my next phase, i gave the pixels mass so they could collide to one other to make planets and stars like in real life, and also i coded orbital mechanics so the would orbit each other relative to their mass but i did not get it to work properly.I generated these quantum pixels with shaders(arcade) because it was a bit too heavy for the cpu…my idea is that a quantum circuit template, stars, planets, galaxies will be generated through these circuitsand the whole universe will be consisted of quantum pixels. bu